OL,3,CProgramme listings for WED 18 MAR
OL,4,G2200F24 Hours in A&E
OL,5,     GThis episode focuses on a young
OL,6,     Ggirl who fell dangerously at a
OL,7,     Gdiving pool, and the difficult
OL,8,     Gwork of the hospital's security
OL,9,     Gteam.
OL,10,G2305F24 Hours in A&E
OL,11,     GTyrell, who's 17, has damaged his
OL,12,     Gbig toe playing football.
OL,13,     GNicholas, who's 26, has been
OL,14,     Gpunched in the face. His jaw is
OL,15,     Gfractured and dislocated and he
OL,16,     Gcan't close his mouth.
OL,17,G0010F999: On the Front Line
OL,18,     GParamedics treat a woman who is
OL,19,     Gin agony with a slipped disc, a
OL,20,     Gman with a chronic lung disease
OL,21,     Gwho can hardly breathe, and a
OL,22,     Gpatient who is unresponsive.
OL,23,Vppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
